<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05188</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR RURAL EMPLOYMENT ASSISTANCE PROGRAM AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Defines the terms “rural area” and “poor” as used in this act; Designates the DSWD to establish and implement the Rural Employment Assistance Program (REAP) , in coordination with the LGUs to provide temporary work to every qualified head of family or an unmarried, single adult member of qualified poor families in rural areas who volunteers to do unskilled manual job for a minimum of 45-90 days in every calendar year.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (086 2017-05-08)</td><td>2. Tambunting (095 2017-05-29)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-11-28</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Approved by the Committee on Appropriations on 2017-11-28</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Substitute Bill to House Bills Numbered 530 and 5188 was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB07266</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON RURAL DEVELOPMENT ON 2017-03-07</td></tr></table>